The paper deals with reasoning in the presence of heterogeneous knowledge sources and data streams, which is a typical problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the computational complexity of various reasoning problems, which is a topic in computational logic (cs.LO). The integration of multiple knowledge sources is a common problem in databases (cs.DB), and the paper also discusses related work in knowledge representation (cs.SE) and stream reasoning (cs.PL).
